1
00:00:07,008 --> 00:00:10,444
⟨I spent days full of love with 50 people who love me →

2
00:00:10,511 --> 00:00:12,446
Detective Manami Tanizaki⟩

3
00:00:12,513 --> 00:00:14,448
⟨From Ai-chan who commits serial murders →

4
00:00:14,515 --> 00:00:17,451
While the battle to protect My Love continues →

5
00:00:17,518 --> 00:00:21,455
A man who claims to be the real culprit appears!

6
00:00:21,522 --> 00:00:26,026
⟨No, there's something in my nose about this guy⟩

7
00:00:27,528 --> 00:00:31,465
>> I call myself Ai-chan →

8
00:00:31,532 --> 00:00:36,971
Killing a person who approached Manami Tanizaki →

9
00:00:37,037 --> 00:00:39,039
I gave instructions.

10
00:00:42,543 --> 00:00:46,981
(Takamine) All about serial murder...?

11
00:00:47,048 --> 00:00:49,984
Well…｡

12
00:00:50,051 --> 00:00:54,488
Let's hear about each incident.

13
00:00:54,555 --> 00:00:56,557
Please wait.

14
00:00:59,060 --> 00:01:04,432
Could you please call Manami Tanizaki?

15
00:01:04,498 --> 00:01:07,935
(Takamine) That's difficult, she's someone involved in the case...

16
00:01:08,002 --> 00:01:10,938
Manami Tanizaki!!

17
00:01:11,005 --> 00:01:14,008
...Could you call me?

18
00:01:16,010 --> 00:01:17,945
(Sound of file closing) Huh…｡

19
00:01:18,012 --> 00:01:22,450
Mr. Kiyosumi lifts Manami Tanizaki's restraint →

20
00:01:22,516 --> 00:01:24,452
Please call me here right now.

21
00:01:24,518 --> 00:01:27,955
(Kiyosumi) Is it okay? >> Okay, hurry up!

22
00:01:28,022 --> 00:01:29,957
(Strong tapping sound)

23
00:01:30,024 --> 00:01:32,460
Understood.

24
00:01:32,526 --> 00:01:34,962
(Sound of door opening and closing)

25
00:01:35,029 --> 00:01:45,473
♪～

26
00:01:45,539 --> 00:01:47,975
(Black Rock) A normal heart A normal heart.

27
00:01:48,042 --> 00:01:50,544
(chime)

28
00:01:52,046 --> 00:01:55,049
(Manami) [Absolutely nothing with Kuroiwa-kun]

29
00:01:57,051 --> 00:01:59,053
(Black Rock) A normal mind!

30
00:02:01,055 --> 00:02:04,492
Huh... are you okay?

31
00:02:05,993 --> 00:02:07,928
(Manami) I feel like dying.

32
00:02:07,995 --> 00:02:11,432
(Kuroiwa) I guess it's because of my abstinence.

33
00:02:11,499 --> 00:02:16,437
(Manami) Um... what kind of business would you give to a sick person?

34
00:02:16,504 --> 00:02:21,442
(Kuroiwa) Ah... a person calling himself Ai-chan has appeared in court.

35
00:02:21,509 --> 00:02:24,445
He said he doesn't talk to anyone except Manami-san.

36
00:02:24,512 --> 00:02:26,013
Huh?

37
00:02:27,014 --> 00:02:28,949
Hey, Manami-san!?

38
00:02:29,016 --> 00:02:31,452
Wow... (Manami) I'll go right away.

39
00:02:31,519 --> 00:02:33,020
(Kuroiwa) Huh?

40
00:02:35,523 --> 00:02:36,957
Oh!

41
00:02:37,024 --> 00:02:40,461
(Manami) I'll blow away Ai-chan! I'll definitely blow it away!

42
00:02:40,528 --> 00:02:42,463
(Kuroiwa) Please investigate.

43
00:02:42,530 --> 00:02:44,965
(Manami) Ai-chan, where are you!?

44
00:02:45,032 --> 00:02:47,968
(Kiyosumi) The tension is terrible. The tension is terrible. It's so tight.

45
00:02:48,035 --> 00:02:49,970
Blinking, blinking, forgetting to blink...

46
00:02:50,037 --> 00:02:51,972
(Takamine) I admit the charges.

47
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:54,475
All that remains is to obtain concrete evidence.

48
00:02:54,542 --> 00:02:57,978
(Manami) But I've never met you!

49
00:02:58,045 --> 00:02:59,980
That... sacred tree? >>Sacred tree.

50
00:03:00,047 --> 00:03:02,483
Is that so?

51
00:03:02,550 --> 00:03:05,419
(Manami) For now, I'll pay my respects.

52
00:03:05,486 --> 00:03:08,923
>> So that tension... Calm down, hey.

53
00:03:08,989 --> 00:03:11,425
(Takamine) Go. (Kuroiwa) Huh?

54
00:03:11,492 --> 00:03:15,429
>> There is a possibility that Manami Tanizaki is in touch with the criminal.

55
00:03:15,496 --> 00:03:17,932
It seems like you are trusted somehow →

56
00:03:17,998 --> 00:03:19,934
I might give out a rag.

57
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,936
(Kuroiwa) No, I don't really have any trust.

58
00:03:22,002 --> 00:03:23,437
>> quickly! (Kuroiwa) Eh...

59
00:03:23,504 --> 00:03:25,940
(Kiyosumi) Go! You... (Kuroiwa) Yes, yes!

60
00:03:26,006 --> 00:03:27,508
It hurt!

61
00:03:36,517 --> 00:03:38,452
(Kamiki) Do you have a cold?

62
00:03:38,519 --> 00:03:39,954
(Manami) Huh?

63
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:45,960
>> Her cheeks look flushed and her breathing is a little rough.

64
00:03:46,026 --> 00:03:48,529
It looks like you have a slight fever.

65
00:03:51,031 --> 00:03:55,536
Sorry, I'm a doctor.

66
00:03:58,539 --> 00:04:01,475
(Manami) I would be in trouble if I was just given a diagnosis.

67
00:04:01,542 --> 00:04:05,980
>> It's true that we can't even give you medicine like this.

68
00:04:08,983 --> 00:04:11,919
I would like him to leave.

69
00:04:11,986 --> 00:04:15,923
(Manami) If he left now, his boss would scold him.

70
00:04:15,990 --> 00:04:17,925
Hey?

71
00:04:17,992 --> 00:04:23,430
>> Is your boss the woman from earlier? (Manami) That's true though.

72
00:04:23,497 --> 00:04:28,435
>> Ah, I'm a little worried about that person. (Kuroiwa) What's going on?

73
00:04:28,502 --> 00:04:31,505
>> Well, no, please don't disturb me.

74
00:04:35,509 --> 00:04:39,947
I'm sorry for the inconvenience, but my name is Yuzuru Kamiki.

75
00:04:40,014 --> 00:04:42,449
I'm a psychiatrist.

76
00:04:42,516 --> 00:04:44,451
(Manami) This is Tanizaki.

77
00:04:44,518 --> 00:04:48,956
>> I wanted to meet you, Manami-san.

78
00:04:49,023 --> 00:04:50,958
(Manami) We've never met before.

79
00:04:51,025 --> 00:04:52,960
>> Yes, there isn't.

80
00:04:53,027 --> 00:04:56,030
(Manami) Then why? >> If we had never met...

81
00:05:01,035 --> 00:05:03,037
Shouldn't you?

82
00:05:04,471 --> 00:05:06,907
Don't start hating it.

83
00:05:06,974 --> 00:05:08,909
(Manami) Do you hate it?

84
00:05:08,976 --> 00:05:13,414
>> Ah... I thought you liked me?

85
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,482
I see, I see. Huh…｡

86
00:05:16,984 --> 00:05:19,420
For those who are popular→

87
00:05:19,486 --> 00:05:22,923
I'm a bit conceited, aren't I?

88
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:25,426
(Manami) Hehe...｡

89
00:05:25,492 --> 00:05:27,928
Ah, I knew it.

90
00:05:27,995 --> 00:05:29,930
Your personality is finished.

91
00:05:29,997 --> 00:05:31,932
>> "As expected" is terrible.

92
00:05:31,999 --> 00:05:35,936
(Manami) Where did I become hated?

93
00:05:36,003 --> 00:05:39,440
>> That's what it feels like!

94
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:42,443
...I had trouble with my mouth.

95
00:05:42,509 --> 00:05:47,448
A pathological playboy who can't even love a single person.

96
00:05:47,514 --> 00:05:51,452
(Manami) I understand that you don't like me.

97
00:05:51,518 --> 00:05:53,954
thank you.

98
00:05:54,021 --> 00:05:58,959
Why did you kill everyone in My Love instead of me?

99
00:05:59,026 --> 00:06:02,963
>> I didn't kill him... (Manami) Instigating murder is the same as murder.

100
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:05,399
>> People who would kill people who would be killed →

101
00:06:05,466 --> 00:06:06,900
I just killed it.

102
00:06:06,967 --> 00:06:11,405
(Manami) Tsk, that kind of thinking is what makes me angry the most.

103
00:06:11,472 --> 00:06:14,908
(Manami's voice) There are people I love who have been killed and suffered.

104
00:06:14,975 --> 00:06:18,412
There are also young people whose futures you have jeopardized.

105
00:06:18,479 --> 00:06:20,914
Killing him will never be forgiven.

106
00:06:20,981 --> 00:06:22,916
But I didn't kill her →

107
00:06:22,983 --> 00:06:25,986
That doesn't mean it's allowed.

108
00:06:27,488 --> 00:06:29,923
>>Then you won't be allowed either.

109
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:34,428
You are the root of all evil.

110
00:06:34,495 --> 00:06:37,498
(Kuroiwa) What position are you speaking from? (Manami) Kuroiwa-kun.

111
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,437
>> Let's talk again tomorrow.

112
00:06:43,504 --> 00:06:47,508
I don't feel like talking anymore today.

113
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:51,945
(Takamine's voice) Is that why you backed down?

114
00:06:52,012 --> 00:06:54,448
(Manami) Even if I continue like that →

115
00:06:54,515 --> 00:06:56,950
You'll just get caught up in the other side's pace.

116
00:06:57,017 --> 00:07:00,954
>> Mr. Tanizaki is the only one who can interrogate Kamiki.

117
00:07:01,021 --> 00:07:03,390
I can't say anything too long.

118
00:07:03,457 --> 00:07:05,893
(Manami) I understand.

119
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:11,398
That's why I want to stay calm and make sure I finish it off.

120
00:07:11,465 --> 00:07:13,901
>> I beg you.

121
00:07:13,967 --> 00:07:15,469
(Manami) Yes...｡

122
00:07:17,471 --> 00:07:20,974
Hmm... I'll buy some medicine.

123
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:27,981
>> Report.

124
00:07:29,483 --> 00:07:32,419
(Kuroiwa) Sacred trees seem formidable.

125
00:07:32,486 --> 00:07:34,988
>> Is there any suspicious behavior from Manami Tanizaki?

126
00:07:36,490 --> 00:07:38,492
(Kuroiwa) There wasn't.

127
00:07:39,993 --> 00:07:44,498
>> Well, that's fine. I'll check the record later.

128
00:07:45,999 --> 00:07:49,503
(Kuroiwa) Um... why did you put Manami up to that point?

129
00:07:51,004 --> 00:07:52,940
>> Because it's questionable.

130
00:07:53,006 --> 00:07:55,008
Is there anything else?

131
00:08:01,515 --> 00:08:04,885
Did it seem like you were interfering with personal matters?

132
00:08:04,952 --> 00:08:06,887
(Kuroiwa) No...

133
00:08:06,954 --> 00:08:09,957
>>Continue monitoring reports.

134
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:15,395
(Kuroiwa) Huh...

135
00:08:15,462 --> 00:08:18,899
(Tsuno) A person who can seriously say that he wants to help people →

136
00:08:18,966 --> 00:08:20,901
There aren't many.

137
00:08:20,968 --> 00:08:22,970
(Manami) Huh...｡

138
00:08:24,471 --> 00:08:26,907
May I see that photo?

139
00:08:26,974 --> 00:08:29,476
>> Ah, this? yes.

140
00:08:30,978 --> 00:08:32,913
(Kimiyo) He's already a saint.

141
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:35,482
He is kind to both patients and us.

142
00:08:38,485 --> 00:08:41,421
(Kuroiwa) Is he a person of character...?

143
00:08:41,488 --> 00:08:45,425
(Manami) On the surface, you can act however you want.

144
00:08:45,492 --> 00:08:47,995
It must have fallen apart somewhere.

145
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:54,935
(Manami) What?

146
00:08:55,002 --> 00:08:59,940
(Kuroiwa) No... Manami-san looking for the bad things about people is refreshing.

147
00:09:00,007 --> 00:09:02,509
(Manami) That's what a detective does.

148
00:09:03,944 --> 00:09:09,383
Honestly, it's going to drive me crazy.

149
00:09:09,449 --> 00:09:11,885
The guy who killed everyone →

150
00:09:11,952 --> 00:09:14,955
You're smiling happily in front of me.

151
00:09:20,961 --> 00:09:25,399
(Manami) But we need to stay calm here.

152
00:09:25,465 --> 00:09:27,467
As a detective.

153
00:09:31,972 --> 00:09:36,410
(Manami) By the way... (Kuroiwa) Yes.

154
00:09:36,476 --> 00:09:42,916
(Manami) Um... Kamiki turned himself in →

155
00:09:42,983 --> 00:09:49,423
Does that mean everyone at My Love can feel safe now?

156
00:09:49,489 --> 00:09:52,926
(Kuroiwa) Ah... to a certain extent.

157
00:09:52,993 --> 00:09:56,930
(Manami) Hmm, then it's about time →

158
00:09:56,997 --> 00:10:02,002
Is it okay to lift the ban?

159
00:10:04,504 --> 00:10:07,941
It's just to regain my composure.

160
00:10:08,008 --> 00:10:10,444
(Kuroiwa) If that helps you get back on track →

161
00:10:10,510 --> 00:10:12,446
Isn't that fine?

162
00:10:12,512 --> 00:10:14,014
(Manami) Hmm...｡

163
00:10:15,515 --> 00:10:17,951
No! I had plans today!

164
00:10:18,018 --> 00:10:20,020
sorry! I'll go home first.

165
00:10:22,522 --> 00:10:24,524
(Kuroiwa) Huh…｡

166
00:10:33,033 --> 00:10:35,902
(Kiryu) The police do nasty things.

167
00:10:35,969 --> 00:10:40,907
(Takamine) [That's a bad guess, even though you're a detective.]

168
00:10:40,974 --> 00:10:43,410
You noticed and let me swim, right?

169
00:10:43,477 --> 00:10:45,479
As expected of a detective.

170
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:48,915
What is the aim?

171
00:10:48,982 --> 00:10:50,917
Manami, are you chasing me?

172
00:10:50,984 --> 00:10:55,422
(Takamine) There's no way I'd tell you, it's investigation information.

173
00:10:55,489 --> 00:10:59,926
Do you remember the phrase “flexible and strong”?

174
00:10:59,993 --> 00:11:04,431
I still put this into practice as a way of conducting investigations.

175
00:11:04,498 --> 00:11:08,001
That's as long as you follow the rules.

176
00:11:09,503 --> 00:11:13,440
This kind of rift in ethics will someday become irreversible.

177
00:11:13,507 --> 00:11:15,942
It's better to turn back now.

178
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:18,011
Well then, please accept my accounting.

179
00:11:20,514 --> 00:11:23,517
Thank you for your advice.

180
00:11:27,521 --> 00:11:30,457
(Manami) My love life is over.

181
00:11:30,524 --> 00:11:33,460
...Or rather, everything was taken away from me.

182
00:11:33,527 --> 00:11:35,395
I really can't forgive it.

183
00:11:35,462 --> 00:11:37,898
(Yuriko) Doesn't that mean you should be quiet?

184
00:11:37,964 --> 00:11:42,402
(Manami) Because of my abstinence, my head is always foggy.

185
00:11:42,469 --> 00:11:44,404
(Iori) What kind of constitution do you have?

186
00:11:44,471 --> 00:11:47,407
(Manami) With this vague head→

187
00:11:47,474 --> 00:11:50,410
I'm scared that I'll be defeated by Kamiki.

188
00:11:50,477 --> 00:11:53,413
>> It's quite formidable, Kamiki.

189
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,415
(Manami) Yes.

190
00:11:55,482 --> 00:11:58,919
But I have to listen carefully.

191
00:11:58,985 --> 00:12:02,989
(Manami's voice) Why did everyone have to die?

192
00:12:04,991 --> 00:12:07,427
>> Good luck!

193
00:12:07,494 --> 00:12:11,431
But it's at times like this that I feel a void in my heart.

194
00:12:11,498 --> 00:12:14,434
Don't let yourself be taken advantage of.

195
00:12:14,501 --> 00:12:19,439
(Manami) Yeah, just stay calm.

196
00:12:19,506 --> 00:12:21,508
📱(3 consecutive received sounds)

197
00:12:23,510 --> 00:12:25,946
(Manami) Ugh! It came.

198
00:12:26,012 --> 00:12:29,516
Three people at once!

199
00:12:30,517 --> 00:12:34,888
It's back! My... My Love Life!

200
00:12:34,955 --> 00:12:37,390
(Yuriko: Iori) Congratulations~｡

201
00:12:37,457 --> 00:12:42,395
(Manami) And it's Ryo-chan! Oh my god!

202
00:12:42,462 --> 00:12:45,398
My love life! My love life!

203
00:12:45,465 --> 00:12:47,467
My life...

204
00:12:48,969 --> 00:12:50,904
(Kuroiwa) Do you know anything?

205
00:12:50,971 --> 00:12:55,408
Plans: How you speak when approached, your personality, etc.

206
00:12:55,475 --> 00:12:57,911
Anything is fine.

207
00:12:57,978 --> 00:13:02,415
(Oikawa) The interrogation isn't going well.

208
00:13:02,482 --> 00:13:04,985
(Toilet flushing sound)

209
00:13:09,990 --> 00:13:14,995
(Oikawa) Huh? Are you going to teach me without anything in return?

210
00:13:16,496 --> 00:13:18,932
(Kuroiwa) Do you understand your position?

211
00:13:18,999 --> 00:13:21,434
>> That's it.

212
00:13:21,501 --> 00:13:25,505
Manami-san, I have to help you, right?

213
00:13:27,007 --> 00:13:29,509
Hey, it's time to go.

214
00:13:31,011 --> 00:13:34,948
(sound of handcuffs being applied)

215
00:13:38,451 --> 00:13:47,894
(birds chirping)

216
00:13:47,961 --> 00:13:53,466
(Manami) The world has regained its color.

217
00:13:54,968 --> 00:13:58,972
Huh... (Emoto) Thank you for your hard work.

218
00:14:00,473 --> 00:14:03,410
(Manami) I feel like I've finally returned to Shaba.

219
00:14:03,476 --> 00:14:07,414
>> Hehe, I'll get ready soon.

220
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:10,417
(Manami) Ah... where are you working now?

221
00:14:10,483 --> 00:14:14,921
>> Ah, it's the library. (Manami) Hmm, nice.

222
00:14:14,988 --> 00:14:16,923
>> Thank you.

223
00:14:16,990 --> 00:14:18,925
It doesn't suit you.

224
00:14:18,992 --> 00:14:22,929
I personally think that heavy lifting suits my gender better.

225
00:14:22,996 --> 00:14:24,998
(Manami) Hehehe...｡

226
00:14:28,501 --> 00:14:34,941
>>But I promised you that I would become weaker because I was willing to die.

227
00:14:36,943 --> 00:14:38,878
(Manami) Yeah...｡

228
00:14:38,945 --> 00:14:42,449
I'll do my best too.

229
00:14:44,451 --> 00:14:46,886
(Kamiki's voice) Don't worry.

230
00:14:46,953 --> 00:14:49,889
My love, no one dies.

231
00:14:49,956 --> 00:14:53,460
As long as I'm here.

232
00:14:55,962 --> 00:15:01,401
(Manami) These are the victims and perpetrators of a series of incidents.

233
00:15:01,468 --> 00:15:05,405
Please tell me how you came into contact with them.

234
00:15:05,472 --> 00:15:07,974
>> Hmm, that's boring.

235
00:15:09,976 --> 00:15:12,979
(Manami) I thought you were going to help me.

236
00:15:14,981 --> 00:15:18,918
You want to help people, right?

237
00:15:18,985 --> 00:15:21,488
>> Ah, did you look into it?

238
00:15:28,495 --> 00:15:32,932
Were you surprised that he was a more personable person than you expected?

239
00:15:32,999 --> 00:15:39,873
Hehe, that's what humans are like.

240
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:42,442
(Manami) What do you want to say?

241
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:46,946
>>It suddenly turns over.

242
00:15:49,449 --> 00:15:52,886
Even if there is no easy-to-understand background →

243
00:15:52,952 --> 00:15:59,459
Good people become bad people...

244
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:03,463
What I don't like is...

245
00:16:05,465 --> 00:16:07,467
I'll love it.

246
00:16:08,968 --> 00:16:11,404
(Manami) Do you want to be liked?

247
00:16:11,471 --> 00:16:14,908
>> What? You hated it? About me.

248
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:17,410
(Manami) It's obvious.

249
00:16:17,477 --> 00:16:19,979
>> I see, that's a shock.

250
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:23,917
No, but→

251
00:16:23,984 --> 00:16:29,989
I think it's just a matter of time to fall in love.

252
00:16:37,931 --> 00:16:42,369
(Manami) You have used sophistry to tame your opponents.

253
00:16:42,435 --> 00:16:46,373
>> Did you also feel like you were being tamed?

254
00:16:46,439 --> 00:16:50,377
Please don't bring me back for questioning.

255
00:16:50,443 --> 00:16:52,445
It's boring.

256
00:16:55,448 --> 00:16:58,385
(Manami) I want to finish it quickly.

257
00:16:58,451 --> 00:17:00,887
This time is a waste.

258
00:17:00,954 --> 00:17:03,890
>> That's a sad thing to say.

259
00:17:03,957 --> 00:17:07,394
This is me →

260
00:17:07,460 --> 00:17:11,898
I hope it will be an unforgettable event for you →

261
00:17:11,965 --> 00:17:13,967
I think so.

262
00:17:17,971 --> 00:17:21,408
(Manami) I'll never forget it. >> Oh, I'm so happy.

263
00:17:21,474 --> 00:17:23,977
(Manami) About the people who died.

264
00:17:26,479 --> 00:17:29,416
I'll forget about you.

265
00:17:29,482 --> 00:17:31,918
I don't want to use my brain's memory.

266
00:17:31,985 --> 00:17:34,988
>> That's a shame...

267
00:17:37,490 --> 00:17:38,925
Ah.

268
00:17:38,992 --> 00:17:43,430
Before I turned myself in, there was one murder I forgot to stop →

269
00:17:43,496 --> 00:17:47,000
It's scheduled to take place today.

270
00:17:51,004 --> 00:17:52,939
(Manami) Who are you trying to kill?

271
00:17:53,006 --> 00:17:55,442
>> That's right, well →

272
00:17:55,508 --> 00:17:59,012
A man who needs to make amends...isn't he?

273
00:18:03,016 --> 00:18:06,085
(Kiyozumi) Huh!? (Kuroiwa) The target is the man who deserves redemption.

274
00:18:06,152 --> 00:18:08,087
>> A man who deserves redemption?

275
00:18:08,154 --> 00:18:10,457
(Kuroiwa) Emossan in the sense of having a criminal record.

276
00:18:10,523 --> 00:18:11,958
(Manami) In other words, Tokujiimo →

277
00:18:12,025 --> 00:18:14,027
Shortly after the war, he was arrested for theft.

278
00:18:14,093 --> 00:18:16,029
>> There are a lot of people who should be compensated!

279
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:18,598
Ah~ Already give everyone security! >> Yes.

280
00:18:21,234 --> 00:18:22,602
\It's the tyranny of power!!/

281
00:18:22,669 --> 00:18:25,171
(Kiyosumi) Huh? Why does he have such a big voice?

282
00:18:33,980 --> 00:18:36,916
This is Takamine from the Metropolitan Police Department.

283
00:18:36,983 --> 00:18:40,420
(Emoto) Social science…｡

284
00:18:40,487 --> 00:18:42,989
Napoleon...

285
00:18:45,492 --> 00:18:48,928
(Matsuno) Huh? What books do you read? you.

286
00:18:48,995 --> 00:18:51,431
Matsuno...

287
00:18:51,498 --> 00:18:52,999
Wow!

288
00:18:54,934 --> 00:18:58,872
You've lost your footing and it's bothering Sakochi.

289
00:18:58,938 --> 00:19:01,875
All the troublesome work will come to me.

290
00:19:01,941 --> 00:19:05,879
Why is this here? >> Ah, I don't feel like talking, sorry.

291
00:19:05,945 --> 00:19:09,449
``Immortal Emoto'' dies of heart failure in a library.

292
00:19:10,950 --> 00:19:13,887
I feel so embarrassed at the end...

293
00:19:13,953 --> 00:19:26,399
♪～

294
00:19:26,466 --> 00:19:27,901
Ugh…｡

295
00:19:27,967 --> 00:19:29,903
(sound of hitting)

296
00:19:29,969 --> 00:19:31,471
(Manami) Ah...｡

297
00:19:33,473 --> 00:19:35,408
Emo-san! Are you okay?

298
00:19:35,475 --> 00:19:37,410
>> Manami-san.

299
00:19:37,477 --> 00:19:39,412
thank you.

300
00:19:39,479 --> 00:19:43,917
(Manami) Ha! I was finally able to protect it.

301
00:19:43,983 --> 00:19:51,925
♪～

302
00:19:51,991 --> 00:19:54,360
>> Were you able to stop it?

303
00:19:54,427 --> 00:19:55,929
(Manami) Yeah.

304
00:19:57,430 --> 00:19:59,365
>> I see.

305
00:19:59,432 --> 00:20:04,871
Well then it's my loss, unfortunately.

306
00:20:04,938 --> 00:20:07,440
(Manami) Do you really think it's a shame?

307
00:20:08,942 --> 00:20:11,377
You could have kept quiet.

308
00:20:11,444 --> 00:20:13,379
This murder plan.

309
00:20:13,446 --> 00:20:16,382
>> Ah, that's certainly true.

310
00:20:16,449 --> 00:20:20,887
(Manami) Compared to the past when she carefully hid her true identity→

311
00:20:20,954 --> 00:20:23,389
Honestly, it's not consistent.

312
00:20:23,456 --> 00:20:25,391
What do you want?

313
00:20:25,458 --> 00:20:31,397
>> Anyway, isn't it good that you were able to protect it?

314
00:20:31,464 --> 00:20:33,466
(Manami) Which mouth...｡

315
00:20:36,469 --> 00:20:38,404
(Kuroiwa) Manami-san.

316
00:20:38,471 --> 00:20:40,406
(Manami) What happened?

317
00:20:40,473 --> 00:20:42,408
(Kuroiwa) The man who attacked Emossan was →

318
00:20:42,475 --> 00:20:44,911
He claims that he has nothing to do with Ai-chan.

319
00:20:44,978 --> 00:20:47,413
>> [Who is it? Call me Ai-chan! ]

320
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:49,482
(Manami) Huh?

321
00:20:50,984 --> 00:20:53,353
(Kuroiwa) And Oikawa →

322
00:20:53,419 --> 00:20:57,423
His body was reportedly found inside the detention center.

323
00:20:58,925 --> 00:21:01,427
(Manami) A man who should make amends...

324
00:21:07,934 --> 00:21:11,437
(Manami) Did you give the instructions to kill Oikawa?

325
00:21:12,939 --> 00:21:15,375
>>Oh, he died.

326
00:21:15,441 --> 00:21:17,377
(Manami) "He died"...

327
00:21:17,443 --> 00:21:19,879
>> Isn't that good?

328
00:21:19,946 --> 00:21:24,884
He's the one who killed my precious friends.

329
00:21:24,951 --> 00:21:27,387
Didn't I say that?

330
00:21:27,453 --> 00:21:30,456
My love says no one dies.

331
00:21:34,961 --> 00:21:38,898
It's been frustrating until now.

332
00:21:38,965 --> 00:21:41,401
My love is an odd relationship →

333
00:21:41,467 --> 00:21:43,903
I'm not even allowed to get really angry.

334
00:21:43,970 --> 00:21:46,406
I just watch helplessly as they are killed.

335
00:21:46,472 --> 00:21:48,408
(Manami) You know... >> Trying to protect it somehow→

336
00:21:48,474 --> 00:21:51,411
When I gathered everyone together, both of them died.

337
00:21:51,477 --> 00:21:53,346
Even if you regret it, you can't regret it.

338
00:21:53,413 --> 00:21:56,416
(Kuroiwa) No! Manami doesn't collect... >> It has nothing to do with you!

339
00:22:01,421 --> 00:22:06,426
I want to help you.

340
00:22:10,430 --> 00:22:14,867
(Manami) In what position... >> I wish I could just stop.

341
00:22:14,934 --> 00:22:17,937
Wouldn't it be difficult if there were a lot of them?

342
00:22:20,940 --> 00:22:22,875
(Manami) Leave me alone.

343
00:22:22,942 --> 00:22:25,878
>> It's okay if you like it!

344
00:22:25,945 --> 00:22:27,947
About me.

345
00:22:34,454 --> 00:22:37,390
(Manami) There's no way that will happen.

346
00:22:37,457 --> 00:22:43,396
>> The likes and dislikes can easily change.

347
00:22:43,463 --> 00:22:49,902
I've already turned over.

348
00:22:49,969 --> 00:22:53,840
I’m sure you too →

349
00:22:53,906 --> 00:22:56,342
you'll love me

350
00:22:56,409 --> 00:23:07,420
♪～
